Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, significant proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, and low serum glucose, suggesting impaired renal function with possible nephrotic-range proteinuria and abnormal glucose handling. Urine is cloudy, brown, and has an ammoniacal odor, but no evidence of infection. Findings are consistent with possible diabetic nephropathy or another glomerular pathology; acute kidney injury cannot be excluded. Clinical correlation and further nephrological evaluation are recommended.
